  "body": "### Description of the Issue\r\n\r\nWhen I try to sign a transaction using MyCrypto, it is incorrectly encoding the transaction.\r\n\r\n### Steps to Reproduce\r\n\r\n1. Open MyCrypto and navigate to the Contracts view, and Interact tab.\r\n1. Put in any address for the Contract Address\r\n1. Fill in the ABI/JSON with:\r\n    ```json\r\n    [\r\n        {\r\n            \"constant\": false,\r\n            \"inputs\": [\r\n                {\r\n                    \"name\": \"tokenAddress\",\r\n                    \"type\": \"address\"\r\n                },\r\n                {\r\n                    \"name\": \"destination\",\r\n                    \"type\": \"address\"\r\n                },\r\n                {\r\n                    \"name\": \"amount\",\r\n                    \"type\": \"uint256\"\r\n                }\r\n            ],\r\n            \"name\": \"sendToken\",\r\n            \"outputs\": [],\r\n            \"payable\": false,\r\n            \"type\": \"function\",\r\n            \"stateMutability\": \"nonpayable\"\r\n        }\r\n    ]\r\n    ```\r\n1. Click Access.\r\n1. Choose `sendToken` method.\r\n1. For the `tokenAddress` put in:\r\n    `0xbaadf00dbaadf00dbaadf00dbaadf00dbaadf00d`\r\n1. For the `destination` put in:\r\n    `0xcafecafecafecafecafecafecafecafecafecafe`\r\n1. For the `amount` put in:\r\n    `1000000000000000000`\r\n1. Fill in any gas price/limit/nonce and click Sign Transaction (I used a ledger).\r\n1. Notice that the raw transaction's data is:\r\n```\r\n0x2fdcfbd20000000000000000000000000000002399f01ad62bc9263b07bb6db1084b9bb500000000000000000000000000000026b07bbbcae5a70c786557f0d75e658a2c0000000000000000000000000000000000000000000000000de0b6b3a7640000\r\n```\r\n\r\n### Description of Your Machine\r\n\r\nWindows 10, MyCrypto desktop app, Ledger Nano.\r\n\r\n### Console Logs / Screenshots\r\n\r\nN/A\r\n\r\n### Discussion\r\n\r\nThe signature is correctly being hashed as the first part of the data, however I expected to see some zeros followed by `baadf00d` repeated as the next 64 characters and some zeros followed by `cafe` repeated as the following 64 characters, finally ending with `0000000000000000000000000000000000000000000000000de0b6b3a7640000` (which is correct, 10**18 in hex).\r\n\r\nI even deleted MyCrypto and re-installed the latest version, so I am pretty confident this isn't a caching issue (my \"reinstall\" mechanism completely blows away everything the MyCrypto installer and app has ever written to disk).\r\n\r\nI tried entering the address with quotes, with and without the `0x` prefix, etc. but nothing seems to make them encode correctly.",
